⚠️ Brutal Truth

If you default to inheritance:

Your system becomes:
Hard to extend
Hard to test
Fragile

If you use composition:

Your system becomes:
Modular
Replaceable
Scalable
🧾 Final Takeaway
Use inheritance only when:
Relationship is stable and obvious
Use composition when:
You expect change (which is almost always)

👉 Industry best practice:

Prefer composition over inheritance

